Legendary musician Ray Phiri s funeral is underway at the Mbombela Stadium in Mpumalanga.Phiri died on the 12 of July 2017, after he succumbed to the battle of Lung cancer at the age of 70.Phiri is accorded with a special provincial official funeral, by the Mpumalanga provincial government.The service started off with the national anthem, which was followed by a musical tribute by internationally acclaimed Lady Smith Black Mambazo.Among mourners who attended the funeral to bed Farwell to the legendary, were Welcome Msomi, Dorothy Masuku and Don Mattera.Ray s son Akhona Phiri gave a moving tribute to his father, on which he told mourners that his father was irreplaceable. Dad you are irreplaceable. Dad, who do I call now, he concluded his tribute.-Sipho Jack